{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "10", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "05", "M": "51", "S": "35"}}, "news": [{"title": "Now, Goa government to offer financial aid for STs to regularise their homes", "para": "Goa government launched a new housing scheme for the Scheduled Tribe community.  This scheme offers financial aid to purchase or regularize dwelling properties.  Assistance covers 100% reimbursement for pre-1972 properties up to one lakh.  Post-1972 properties receive 50% reimbursement, also capped at one lakh.  Eligibility requires belonging to the ST community and having an annual family income below five lakh.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/now-goa-government-to-offer-financial-aid-for-sts-to-regularise-their-homes/132302222?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1226434/132302222.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Meghalaya cabinet approves second IT park building in New Shillong", "para": "The Meghalaya cabinet approved revised administrative approval for a second IT park building. This expansion will add plug-and-play office space and modern facilities. The government also approved the establishment of St Xavier's University in the state. Fifty acres of land were allotted at Mawkhanu for the university. These decisions aim to boost higher education and job opportunities for youth.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/meghalaya-cabinet-greenlights-new-it-park-and-st-xaviers-university-in-shillong/132302199?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1924644/132302199.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Jan Vishwas Bill brings major regulatory overhaul, land conversion & urban planning in Assam", "para": "Assam tabled a bill to amend six state Acts, reducing regulatory compliance. This initiative aims to simplify approvals and improve ease of doing business. The bill proposes changes in education, planning, fire services, and land reclassification. It also seeks to align fire safety norms with national building standards. Amendments will simplify cinema regulation and land use change procedures.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/assams-jan-vishwas-bill-a-game-changer-in-regulatory-compliance-and-urban-planning/132302158?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2087283/132302158.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}